---
// LocalGuide.astro — Itinerary journal style, NOT a listicle
---
<section class="guide" id="guide">
  <div class="guide__header">
    <span class="label">Local Guide</span>
    <h2 class="headline guide__title">
      The forest<br />has its own<br /><em>schedule</em>
    </h2>
    <p class="guide__intro">
      What follows is not a list of attractions. It is a partial map of how we spend
      our own time here — the trails that reward the slow walker, the waters that are
      best at dawn, the meal at the end of a full day.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="guide__entries">
    <!-- Entry: Dawn -->
    <div class="guide__entry reveal">
      <div class="guide__entry-time">
        <span class="guide__time-num">05</span>
        <span class="guide__time-ampm">AM</span>
      </div>
      <div class="guide__entry-body">
        <h3 class="guide__entry-title">The Hermit Trail — before the world wakes</h3>
        <p class="guide__entry-text">
          Three miles through second-growth fir. The trailhead is a ten-minute walk from the property's
          east gate. By the time the first light reaches the forest floor, you will have passed the old
          cedar that fell in 2019 — still standing in its own absence — and the creek that runs cold
          enough to ache. The turnaround is a platform of old-growth nurse log, wide enough to sit on.
          Bring the field guide. Leave the phone.
        </p>
        <div class="guide__entry-meta">
          <span class="guide__tag">Trail</span>
          <span class="guide__tag">3.2 miles</span>
          <span class="guide__tag">Moderate</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="guide__entry-media">
        <img
          src="/images/gallery-forest-calm.jpg"
          alt="Morning mist in old-growth forest, Pacific Northwest"
        />
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Entry: Morning -->
    <div class="guide__entry reveal">
      <div class="guide__entry-time">
        <span class="guide__time-num">09</span>
        <span class="guide__time-ampm">AM</span>
      </div>
      <div class="guide__entry-body">
        <h3 class="guide__entry-title">Breakfast at the property — whatever the forager brought</h3>
        <p class="guide__entry-text">
          Our kitchen operates on a single rule: the menu is decided before dawn, by the person who
          walks the property at first light. What you eat depends on the season, the weather, and the
          previous night's inventory from our neighboring farms. In spring, there are wild nettles and
          ramps. In summer, early tomatoes from the hoop house and eggs from the hen operation two fields
          over. Coffee is from a small roaster in Portland; it arrives by mail and we consider it part
          of the landscape.
        </p>
        <div class="guide__entry-meta">
          <span class="guide__tag">On-site</span>
          <span class="guide__tag">Seasonal menu</span>
          <span class="guide__tag">Farm partners</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="guide__entry-media">
        <img
          src="/images/timeline-yoga.jpg"
          alt="Morning breakfast — seasonal, foraged, local"
        />
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Entry: Afternoon — full width cinematic -->
    <div class="guide__entry guide__entry--full reveal">
      <div class="guide__entry-media-full">
        <img
          src="/images/hero-misty-path.jpg"
          alt="Mountain lake in the North Cascades — afternoon light"
        />
      </div>
      <div class="guide__entry-content-full">
        <div class="guide__entry-time">
          <span class="guide__time-num">14</span>
          <span class="guide__time-ampm">PM</span>
        </div>
        <div class="guide__entry-body">
          <h3 class="guide__entry-title">The Glass Lake — a forty-minute drive, worth every minute</h3>
          <p class="guide__entry-text">
            No motors. No development on the far shore. The lake sits in a basin carved by the last
            glaciation, and on calm days the surface holds the surrounding peaks so precisely that the
            reflection looks more real than the mountains themselves. We have a canoe. You may take it.
            Bring a sandwich from the kitchen; they'll pack one if you ask the night before. Return in
            time for dinner, or don't, and we'll keep a plate warm.
          </p>
          <div class="guide__entry-meta">
            <span class="guide__tag">Drive: 40 min</span>
            <span class="guide__tag">Canoe available</span>
            <span class="guide__tag">Pack a lunch</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Entry: Evening -->
    <div class="guide__entry reveal">
      <div class="guide__entry-time">
        <span class="guide__time-num">19</span>
        <span class="guide__time-ampm">PM</span>
      </div>
      <div class="guide__entry-body">
        <h3 class="guide__entry-title">The Fire Pit — when dusk becomes an event</h3>
        <p class="guide__entry-text">
          Every evening, between October and mid-April, the fire is lit before dinner service begins.
          The pit sits in a clearing between the main building and the tree line, positioned so that
          the smoke draws toward the forest rather than across the terrace. We supply locally made
          wool blankets in case the temperature drops. The kitchen sends out small plates throughout
          the evening — not as a formal tasting menu, but as what the cook felt like making.
        </p>
        <div class="guide__entry-meta">
          <span class="guide__tag">Seasonal</span>
          <span class="guide__tag">Oct–Apr</span>
          <span class="guide__tag">Small plates</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="guide__entry-media">
        <img
          src="/images/packages-tea.jpg"
          alt="Evening fire pit in the forest, warm light and wool blankets"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
/* ── Easing ── */
.guide {
  --ease-standard: cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1);
  --ease-spring:   cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.56, 0.64, 1);
}

.guide {
  background: var(--cream);
  padding: var(--space-2xl) 0;
}

.guide__header {
  max-width: 1000px;
  margin: 0 auto 6rem;
  padding: 0 2rem;
}

.guide__title {
  margin: 1rem 0 2rem;
  color: var(--ink);
}

.guide__title em {
  font-style: italic;
  color: var(--green);
}

.guide__intro {
  font-family: var(--serif);
  font-size: 1.1rem;
  font-style: italic;
  color: var(--green-mid);
  line-height: 1.6;
  max-width: 640px;
}

/* Entries */
.guide__entries {
  max-width: 1300px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 0 2rem;
}

.guide__entry {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 5rem 1fr 1fr;
  gap: 0 3rem;
  padding: 4rem 0;
  border-top: 1px solid rgba(74,93,74,0.12);
  align-items: start;
}

.guide__entry:last-child {
  border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(74,93,74,0.12);
}

/* Full width cinematic entry */
.guide__entry--full {
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  gap: 0;
  padding: 0;
  border-top: none;
  margin-bottom: 0;
}

.guide__entry--full .guide__entry-media-full {
  position: relative;
  min-height: 600px;
}

.guide__entry--full .guide__entry-media-full img {
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
}

.guide__entry-content-full {
  background: var(--cream-dark);
  padding: 4rem 3.5rem;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  justify-content: center;
}

.guide__entry-time {
  display: flex;
  align-items: baseline;
  gap: 0.4rem;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}

/* Amber gradient time numbers */
.guide__time-num {
  font-family: var(--serif);
  font-size: 3.5rem;
  font-weight: 300;
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--amber-light) 0%, var(--amber-dark) 100%);
  -webkit-background-clip: text;
  -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
  background-clip: text;
  line-height: 1;
  transition: transform 0.4s var(--ease-spring);
}

.guide__entry:hover .guide__time-num {
  transform: translateY(-2px);
}

.guide__time-ampm {
  font-size: 0.7rem;
  font-weight: 500;
  letter-spacing: 0.15em;
  color: var(--green-mid);
}

.guide__entry-title {
  font-family: var(--serif);
  font-size: 1.4rem;
  font-weight: 400;
  color: var(--ink);
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
  line-height: 1.3;
}

.guide__entry-text {
  font-size: 0.9rem;
  color: var(--ink-light);
  line-height: 1.8;
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
}

.guide__entry-meta {
  display: flex;
  gap: 1rem;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
}

.guide__tag {
  font-size: 0.65rem;
  font-weight: 500;
  letter-spacing: 0.15em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--green-mid);
  padding: 0.3rem 0.75rem;
  border: 1px solid rgba(74,93,74,0.2);
  border-radius: 2px;
  transition: all 0.3s var(--ease-standard);
}

.guide__entry:hover .guide__tag {
  border-color: var(--amber);
  color: var(--amber-dark);
}

.guide__entry-media {
  overflow: hidden;
}

/* Spring hover on entry images */
.guide__entry-media img {
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
  min-height: 280px;
  transition: transform 0.7s var(--ease-spring);
}

.guide__entry:hover .guide__entry-media img {
  transform: scale(1.04);
}

@media (max-width: 1024px) {
  .guide__entry {
    grid-template-columns: 4rem 1fr;
    gap: 0 2rem;
  }

  .guide__entry-media {
    display: none;
  }

  .guide__entry--full {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .guide__entry--full .guide__entry-media-full {
    min-height: 380px;
    position: relative;
  }

  .guide__entry-content-full {
    padding: 3rem 2rem;
  }
}

@media (max-width: 640px) {
  .guide__entry {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .guide__entry-time {
    flex-direction: row;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .guide__time-num {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
  }
}
</style>